metadata.name: Inconsolable Interface
metadata.description:
I once imagined feelings about the world

these existed at both the community
and societal level and were not dependent
on how I processed things

I imaged a long lake bright
in the sun that reflected glancing blows on
a park wall

I colored it green then blue then white with
the morning I painted 
graffiti in lurid hues that said things I could never
to my mother I sat on a bench and waited

for the scene and the feelings to subside

--

2022, wall, plasticine, Windows 95 emulator, Figma, 3DC, noise engine, Photoshop
5376 x 6399
